cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper is about neural architecture search (NAS) for computer vision tasks, specifically on CIFAR-10 and ImageNet datasets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as differentiable NAS, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of neural architectures, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of hardware metrics for architecture design could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
